      "28",
      "34",
      "32"
    ],
    "correct_option": 2,
    "solution_text": "Given :\nIf 4 ⊕ 3 = 19 and 5 ⊕ 2 = 17\nLogic : (1st number × 2nd number) + (1st number + 2nd number) = 3rd number\nFor, 4 ⊕ 3 = 19\n(4 × 3) + (4 + 3) = 12 + 7 = 19\nFor, 5 ⊕ 2 = 17\n(5 × 2) + (5 + 2) = 10 + 7 = 17\nSimilarly,\n6 ⊕ 4 = ?\n(6 × 4) + (6 + 4) = 24 + 10 = 34\nThus, correct option is (c)."
  },
