    "correct_option": 2,
    "solution_text": "Given :\nGiven Sign +×\nNew Sign -÷\nUsing BODMAS rule.\nNow, we check each options.\nOption (a):  8 − 2 + 3 = 12 (Correct)\n= 8 ÷ 2 × 3\n= 4 × 3\n= 12\n Option (b):  6 + 3 − 2 = 9 (Correct)  \n= 6 × 3 ÷ 2\n= 18 ÷ 2\n= 9\n Option (c):  4 − 2 + 5 = 15 (Incorrect)  \n= 4 ÷ 2 × 5\n= 2 × 5\n= 10  15 \n Option (d):  9 + 1 − 3 = 3 (Correct)  \n= 9 × 1 ÷ 3\n= 9 ÷ 3\n= 3\nThus, correct option is (c).   Operation preference wise\nBrackets\nOrders, of\nDivision\nMultiplication\nAddition\nSubtractionSymbol\n[],,()\n(power),√(root),of\n÷\n×\n+\n−\n="
