    "solution_text": "The correct answer is (c) 104th Amendment.\nExplanation:\n• The 104th Constitutional Amendment Act, 2019  ended the nomination of Anglo-Indian members  to State Legislative Assemblies.\n• It retained reservation for SCs and STs , but discontinued Anglo-Indian nomination after 70 years  of the Constitution.\nInformation Booster :\n• The original provision was under Article 333 .\n• The amendment came into force in January 2020 .\n• Anglo-Indian nomination to the Lok Sabha  was also abolished.\n• Reservation for SC/ST s was extended for 10 more years .\nAdditional Knowledge :\n• The Governor earlier had discretionary power to nominate Anglo-Indians if underrepresented.\n• This change reflects evolving demographic and political considerations .\n\nCopyright © 2026  Adda247"
