    "exam": "SSC CGL",
    "subject": "General Knowledge",
    "subtopic": "General Knowledge",
    "chapter": "Current Affairs",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "question_text": "Which is generally not classified as a w eather p aramet er?",
    "options": [
      "Temperature",
      "Humidity",
      "Soil pH",
      "Wind"
    ],
    "correct_option": 2,
    "solution_text": "The correct answer is (c) Soil pH.\nExplanation:\n• Weather parameters  describe the state of the atmosphere at a given time and place.\n• Temperature, humidity, and wind  are atmospheric variables and are core weather elements.\n• Soil pH  relates to soil chemistry  and agricultural science, not atmospheric conditions.\nInformation Booster :\n• Major weather parameters include temperature, atmospheric pressure, humidity, wind speed/direction, and precipitation .\n• Weather is studied by meteorology , while soil properties fall under pedology/agricultural science .\n• Weather conditions can change hourly or daily , unlike soil pH which changes slowly.\n• Instruments: thermometer (temperature), hygrometer (humidity), anemometer (wind).\nAdditional Knowledge :\n• Soil pH  influences crop productivity and nutrient availability , not weather forecasting.\n• Climate studies consider long-term averages of weather parameters, still excluding soil chemistry.\n• Soil pH becomes relevant in agro-climatic studies , but not as a direct weather parameter."
  },
