    "exam": "SSC CGL",
    "subject": "English",
    "subtopic": "English Language",
    "chapter": "Miscellaneous",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "question_text": "Choose the most suitable option t o replace the highlight ed part of the sent ence:\nNo one knows where is he staying .",
    "options": [
      "where is he stay",
      "where he is staying at",
      "where he is staying",
      "where he had stayed is"
    ],
    "correct_option": 2,
    "solution_text": "The correct option is (c).\nExplanation : The given sentence is an embedded (indir ect) question  after the clause “No one knows...”. In embedded questions, we do not use\nquestion word order (auxiliary + subject). Instead, we use statement w ord order (subject + verb).\nIncorrect: “where is he staying ” (question order)\nCorrect: “where he is staying ” (statement order)\nGrammatical rule used :\nIn indirect questions after verbs like know , ask, wonder , tell, the structure is: Wh-w ord + subject + v erb.\nDo not place the auxiliary before the subject in indirect questions.\nExample (rule demonstration) : I don’t know wher e she liv es. (Not: where does she live.)\nWhy other options ar e incorr ect:\nOption A : Grammatically incorrect phrase; “stay” form is wrong and question order remains incorrect.\nOption B : Unnecessary and incorrect addition of “at”; “stay” generally does not require “at” in this structure.\nOption D : Wrong tense and incorrect structure; “is” at the end makes the clause ungrammatical.\nSo the correct answer is (c)"
  },
